<title type="html"><![CDATA[Let us use FRAMES]]></title>

<content type="html" xml:base="https://forums.whatwg.org/bb3/viewtopic.php?t=145&amp;p=5437#p5437"><![CDATA[
The W3C Working Draft states that: &quot;The following elements are not in HTML 5 because their usage affected usability and accessibility for the end user in a negative way: frame, frameset, noframes&quot; <br /><br />Anyone can make an unusable and unaccessible site using using any tool available and all other &quot;good&quot; tags approved for HTML5. If we have messy sites on the internet, fames and framesets are not to be blamed. Those who did a bad job should be responsible for that. <br /><br />I believe these 3 tags should stay on HTML5. No one is forced do use them. We can use them wisely without negatively affecting usability and accessibility. DonÂ´t let the bad work of a few programmers and web designers prevent all the others from using these tags.<p>Statistics: Posted by <a href="https://forums.whatwg.org/bb3/memberlist.php?mode=viewprofile&amp;u=777">pedro80</a> — Sun Dec 06, 2009 7:15 pm</p><hr />
